      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ten years of effort collapsing into fraud feels absolute, but history shows that even Nobel laureates have corrected single fatal errors without ending their legacies. Your identity extends far beyond a specific theory because your resilience in seeking truth already defines you as more than a ghost. Sometimes stepping away to heal is the strongest foundation needed before you can rebuild a career or find new direction. This darkness is real right now, but it does not erase the scientist who fought diligently when hope seemed impossible.",
      "source": "target",
