      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Validation comes not from rebuilding immediately, but from acknowledging that grief over lost identity is a profound and valid part of the healing process when scientific crusades collapse this severely. Even ghosts have stories that matter because the effort of walking through the darkness proves you were real even if your theories erode away today. Sometimes the only responsible step forward is to rest within that hollow shell until the noise stops screaming before seeking a future again. Your worth wasn't written solely in papers, but in the sheer courage it took to pursue truth despite an error you couldn't see at the time.",
